Upon approval of your application, the Office of the Treasurer and Tax Collector will send a registration certificate, which must be conspicuously displayed at your place of business. 
 
 You ARE REQUIRED to file a San Francisco Gross Receipts and Payroll Expense Tax Annual Return (?Return?) for tax year 2016 if you are: 
 ? A business with more than $150,000 in San Francisco payroll expense; OR 
 ? A business with more than $500,000 in San Francisco gross receipts; OR 
 ? A lessor of residential real estate (residential landlord) renting four or more units"

status_notes:
The Mayor's Office of Housing does not administer Section 8, provide emergency shelter, or manage affordable rental housing. The contact office is the San Francisco Housing Authority at 1815 Egbert Avenue, SF CA 94124, (415) 715-3280. The US Department Housing and Urban Development (HUD) oversees the Housing Authority, 600 Harrison St. 3rd Floor San Francisco, CA 94107-1300. Their main phone number is (415) 489-6400 and all SFHA complaints at (415) 489-6448.
 
 The mission of the Mayor's Office of Housing is to provide financing for the development, rehabilitation and purchase of affordable housing in San Francisco. MOH also guides and coordinates the City's housing policy. MOH administers a variety of programs to finance the development of affordable housing by non-profit and for profit developers, provides financial and educational assistance to first-time homebuyers, and finances housing rehabilitation costs for low-income homeowners. MOH is also responsible for monitoring and ensuring the long-term affordability and physical viability of the City's stock of affordable housing.

 Dear Samedy,
 
 
 In response to your question regarding changing your business name, you need to first clarify whether you are changing Trade Name/DBA name or the Ownership name. Please look at the business information stated on your San Francisco Business Registration Certificate.
 
 
 Changing the Trade Name/DBA (Doing Business As) name:
 
 - You can update it at our online business information update link at our website by selecting "adding a business location" and indicate the new business name for that business location. 
 
 Below is the link to our online update:
 
 https://etaxstatement.sfgov.org/accountupdate/
 
 Changing/updating the "Ownership" Name is not allowed in the existing business account.
 
 - You may not update this information. This requires you to open a new business registration account under the new ownership name.
 
 
 **However, if you meet the circumstances, you may submit change request by mail, in-person, or fax a completed Update Business Information Paper Form (see attachment) and you must be able to provide/include both documentations below:
 
 1) Letter from the Secretary of State verifying transfer/change of the old ownership business name to the new ownership business name.
 
 2) Letter from the IRS stating the same tax EIN number has been transferred from the old ownership name to the new ownership business name.
 
 You need to complete the "other changes to account information" section of the paper form.\

status_notes:
Emailed:
Dirty or discolored (rusty, yellow, brown) is typically caused by sediments that have become stirred up inside of a water main or pipe. Any increase in water velocity through a pipe or main can cause increased friction against pipe walls that can stir up sediments. Common causes are main breaks, shutdown of a facility, loss of pressure or the opening of a fire hydrant in the immediate area.
Recommendation
First, avoid using your hot water so that you dont draw discolored water into your water heater or boiler. Next check to see if the water supplying your home or business is clear or dirty/discolored. To do this, open a tap (cold water) on the ground floor as close to your water meter (located in the sidewalk) as possible. Typically this would be a hose bibb in front of the house or just inside the garage door, or a downstairs utility sink. Run the water for 3-5 minutes to see if it runs clear. If not, turn off the tap and repeat periodically about every 45-60 minutes. You should see your water progressively clear. It may take several hours depending upon the severity of the discoloration. When the water runs clear at the ground floor tap, flush out your plumbing by opening faucets and flushing toilets inside your home or business. If your hot water does not run clear, it is possible that the dirty/discolored water has entered water heater or boiler. For safety reasons it is recommended that you call PG&E or a plumber to flush the water heater or boiler.
